<div class=3D"sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content=3D"">
  <p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">Booking ahead is another sm=
art strategy for many transportation options including flights using points=
 (start looking a year out), trains in Europe, and anything that goes on sa=
le. While I don=E2=80=99t want to encourage <a href=3D"https://www.travelbu=
gtonic.com/blog/travel-planning-advice" target=3D"_blank" data-modified-hre=
f=3D"https://www.travelbugtonic.com/blog/travel-planning-advice">overplanni=
ng a trip</a>, if you identify the key transportation routes and create a s=
tructure for your itinerary, you can secure train, bus, or ferry tickets ea=
rly, often with an advanced booking discount, and gain peace of mind knowin=
g your travel arrangements are in place.&nbsp;<br><br>Watch for annual sale=
s on travel. Black Friday and Boxing Day are notorious for having great pri=
ces on flights or tours, so be prepared to press buy if something aligns wi=
th your plans. I scored a great discount on <a href=3D"https://www.eurail.c=
om/" target=3D"_blank" data-modified-href=3D"https://www.eurail.com/">Eurai=
l</a> passes during their anniversary sale. I wasn=E2=80=99t going to be us=
ing them for 10 months, but I took advantage of the great price and by the =
time my trip came around, they had been bought and paid for!<br></p>
