  <h4 style=3D"margin-left:40px;white-space:pre-wrap;">The Slower the Bette=
r</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">My personal opinion is =
that travel experiences are enhanced when you slow down! This includes taki=
ng trains instead of flying, using buses instead of taxis, and walking when=
ever possible. Public transportation systems in European cities are typical=
ly excellent and city passes or transportation cards can offer further disc=
ounted fares on buses, trams, metros and trains. While these choices often =
create a few more travel wrinkles and take more time, they enrich your expe=
rience of a place. I=E2=80=99d argue that anyone who doesn't take public tr=
ansportation in a new city is missing out!<br><br><a href=3D"https://www.tr=
avelbugtonic.com/blog/new-rhythm" target=3D"_blank" data-modified-href=3D"h=
