<div class=3D"sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content=3D"">
  <h4 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">Case Study</h4><p class=3D"" style=3D=
"white-space:pre-wrap;">Let me use our =E2=80=9Cretirement=E2=80=9D trip as=
 an example. By applying all the money-saving strategies and using the Trav=
el Budget Calculator to sort our expenses, we discovered that we spent a to=
tal of $9000 for 10 weeks - an average of $900/week for two people. This is=
 the breakdown of where our money went:</p><p style=3D"margin-left:40px;whi=
te-space:pre-wrap;" class=3D"sqsrte-small"><strong>~10% transportation</str=
ong> - trains, buses, and flights <em>(Victoria - Barcelona, Sevilla - Port=
o, Lisbon - Bordeaux return, Lisbon - Victoria)</em></p><p style=3D"margin-=
left:40px;white-space:pre-wrap;" class=3D"sqsrte-small"><strong>~32% accomm=
odation</strong> - 5 nights using travel rewards, two 1-month stays with 40=
% discounts, and a =E2=80=9Cfree=E2=80=9D week away using <a href=3D"https:=
//www.travelbugtonic.com/blog/how-does-home-exchange-work" target=3D"_blank=
" data-modified-href=3D"https://www.travelbugtonic.com/blog/how-does-home-e=
xchange-work">Home Exchange</a>.</p><p style=3D"margin-left:40px;white-spac=
e:pre-wrap;" class=3D"sqsrte-small"><strong>~33% food</strong> - we spend a=
 bit less than this normally at home with a combination of groceries and ea=
ting out! So using =E2=80=9Ctraveller=E2=80=99s math=E2=80=9D - does that e=
ven count!?!?=F0=9F=98=85</p><p style=3D"margin-left:40px;white-space:pre-w=
rap;" class=3D"sqsrte-small"><strong>~ 19% activities</strong> - walking an=
d food tours, entrance fees, 2 cooking classes, futbol tickets, a flamenco =
show - ALL the things we wanted to do!</p><p style=3D"margin-left:40px;whit=
e-space:pre-wrap;" class=3D"sqsrte-small">~6% =E2=80=9Cother=E2=80=9D - <a =
href=3D"https://airalo.pxf.io/b3xq0g" target=3D"_blank" data-modified-href=
=3D"https://airalo.pxf.io/b3xq0g">Airalo e-sim cards</a>, travel insurance,=
 gifts, etc=E2=80=A6</p><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">I sha=
re this not to say that these percentages are a target. Instead, I hope you=
 see that YOU can customize and juggle travel expenses in these four catego=
ries to make sure that you can:</p><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-w=
rap;">a) find a way to afford travel.</p><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space=
:pre-wrap;">b) spend money on the things that most matter to you.</p><p cla=
ss=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">c) learn about your spending habits=
