<div class=3D"sqs-html-content" data-sqsp-text-block-content=3D"">
  <h2 style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">What NOT to Scrimp and Save on</h2><p=
 class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">There are a few things I don=E2=
=80=99t recommend skipping or compromising just to save money.</p><p class=
=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;"><strong>#1 Travel medical insurance</=
strong></p><p class=3D"" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">This is a must! Se=
riously - don=E2=80=99t think about hedging your bets on staying healthy or=
 avoiding an accident because you just never know! My husband and I had one=
 trip that sadly included an ambulance ride, 2 hospital visits, 26 stitches=
, a consult with a plastic surgeon, and pain medications. (And a new ballca=
p to hide the bandaged head!) Thank goodness for insurance!</p><p class=3D"=
" style=3D"white-space:pre-wrap;">I=E2=80=99d also recommend ensuring you h=
ave trip cancellation coverage. <a href=3D"https://www.travelbugtonic.com/b=
log/trip-cancellation" target=3D"_blank" data-modified-href=3D"https://www.=
travelbugtonic.com/blog/trip-cancellation">Read about my experience cancell=
ing a trip</a>.</p>
</div>




















